{
  "texts": [
    "A very general implementation of these ideas for the reconstruction of cluster lenses is the GRALE code (introduced by Liesenborgs et al. 2006 Liesenborgs et al., 2007, with many later enhancements).",
    "In GRALE each model consists of a large number of Plummer lenses (Eq.",
    "(56)) and there is an ensemble or population of models that evolves according to a genetic algorithm to fit the lensing data.",
    "The prior is implicitly defined by the algorithm rather than explicit, but is minimal: the mass distribution must be non-negative.",
    "The likelihood is not Gaussian, however it does incorporate the data on image locations and shapes, and also the absence of lensed images where they are not observed."
  ]
}